The owner shall document that all representative interior unit painted surfaces and all representative exterior painted surfaces that can reasonably be considered as the unit’s exterior surfaces have been tested by a lead-based paint inspector or
        risk assessor and do not contain lead based paint. For purposes of this paragraph, painted surfaces that can reasonably be considered as the unit’s exterior surfaces include balcony and terrace components, exterior window and door components,
        and any accessible exterior wall surfaces that are part of the structure of the unit;
